         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#jmr-jbwp-rgg2003" xml:lang="en"><p>Greetings, fortunate Hesychios!</p></div>
            </div>
    
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>A favourable acclamation (greetings) and not a sepulcral formula (farewell). </p><p> 
               For Hesychios see <ref type="inscription">C02200</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C07100</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C59400</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C69000</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C69700</ref>.
               Καλόκερος (= Καλόκαιρος)  a name of good omen (see <bibl><author>Robert</author>, <title>Hellenica</title> 
                  <citedRange>IX</citedRange>, <citedRange>64.f</citedRange></bibl>),
               is apparently being used as an epithet. <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἡσύχιος</foreign>, meaning 'tranquil' indicates 
               a clearly related idea in the mind of the name-giver.</p>
         </div>
         
